{{Infobox award | name = Bluetech International Clean Air Technology Award | image = | image_size = <!-- or | image_upright = --> | alt = | caption = | description = | sponsor = Clean Air Alliance of China | date = <!-- {{start date|2015|12|12}} --> | location = <!-- or | venue = or | site = --> | country = China | presenter = | host = <!-- or | hosts = --> | former name = | website = <!-- {{URL|en.bluetechaward.com}} --> }} The '''Bluetech International Clean Air Technology Award''' (also called '''Bluetech Award'''), is an annual award presented by the [[Clean Air Alliance of China]] (CAAC) to recognize outstanding technologies that prevent and control different forms and sources of [[air pollution]]. The award examines each technology for breakthrough potential in terms of technological performance,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.environmentalleader.com/2015/09/clean-air-tech-competition-seeks-pollution-treatment-providers/|title=Clean Air Tech Competition Seeks Pollution Treatment Providers|first=Jessica Lyons|last=Hardcastle|date=4 September 2015|publisher=}}</ref> environmental impact, and financial feasibility with CAAC’s standardized technology assessment methodology.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.cleanairchina.org/channel/type/70-3079-1.html?menuId=0|title=Products - Clean Air Alliance of China|publisher=}}</ref> The award selection committee consists of technical professionals, industrial experts and testing specialists that are chosen every year to fit each year’s award categories. Technologies from around the world are eligible to apply.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thebeijinger.com/blog/2015/08/27/bluetech-award-competition-clean-air-companies-join-fight-against-air-pollution|title=Clean Air Tech Competition Aims to Accelerate Fight Against Air Pollution in China|first=|last=schreursm|date=27 August 2015|publisher=}}</ref>
The award ceremony, called the Bluetech International Clean Air Forum, features research leaders, industries, investors and policymakers in [[China]] and abroad to address global industry and policy trends in the air quality sector. Private follow-up events, held in [[Beijing]] and other pilot regions, are organized for Alliance members and selected technology companies. The first Bluetech Award Ceremony was held on December 12, 2015, in Beijing, China. The second Bluetech Award Ceremony is planned for December 2016.{{citation needed|date=June 2016}}
