{{redirect|Yarullin|other people with this surname|Yarullin (surname)}} [[Image:Farit Yarullin.jpg|thumb|200px|right|Färit Yarullin]] '''Yarullin Färit Zahidulla ulı''' (pronounced {{IPA-tt|jʌrˈulʲin fæˈrit zɑhidulˈlɑː uˈlɯ|}}{{Dubious|date=November 2008}}) aka '''Färit Yarullin'''; [[Tatar language|Tatar Cyrillic]]: Яруллин Фәрит Заһидулла улы; {{lang-ru|Яру́ллин Фари́д Загиду́ллович}}, '''Yarullin Farid Zagidullovich'''; 1914 &ndash; 1943) was a [[Tatar]] composer, the creator of the first Tatar [[ballet]], ''[[Şüräle]]''. His works include chamber music, romances, songs and arrangement of folk music. He participated in [[World War II]] and was killed in action in 1943.
In 1958, fifteen years after his death, he became a [[Ğabdulla Tuqay]] [[TASSR]] [[State Prizes of the Soviet Republics|State Prize]] laureate.
