The '''Tambanuo''' (or '''Tombonuo''') people are an [[indigenous peoples|indigenous]] [[ethnic group]] residing in [[Sabah]], eastern [[Malaysia]] on the island of [[Borneo]]. They reside in [[Beluran]], [[Kota Marudu]], and [[Pitas, Malaysia|Pitas]] districts of [[Kudat Division]] of Sabah. Their population was estimated at 20,000 in the year 1990. They are considered a sub-group of the [[Orang Sungai]], and their language ([[ISO 639-3]] txa) belongs to the Paitanic branch of the [[Austronesian languages|Austronesian]] language family.

